### Example 2: Matches NetBackup status code 2106
**Input fields:**
| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Short Description | Multiple backup jobs failing - storage server down |
| Description | Since this morning, all backup jobs targeting cloud storage are failing. Activity monitor shows the storage unit as unavailable. We did certificate maintenance on the media servers last week. |
| Error Code | 2106 |
| Work Notes | Verified CloudStore Service running on master server. Need to check media server. Cloud tier to AWS S3 is affected. Possible stale certificates on media server after last week's cert work. |
| Configuration Item | NBU-MS-WIN-PC03 |
| Category | Storage |
| Product Name | Veritas NetBackup 10.1.1 Master Server |
| Product Bar Code | *(empty)* |
| Serial Number | *(empty)* |

**Formatted search query:**
ISSUE: Backup jobs failing with status code 2106 indicating disk storage server is down
SYMPTOMS: Multiple backup jobs failing simultaneously, storage unit unavailable in activity monitor, cloud storage tiering jobs to AWS S3 failing
ERROR: Status Code 2106 — Disk storage server is down
SYSTEM: Veritas NetBackup 10.1.1 Master Server (NBU-MS-WIN-PC03)
CATEGORY: Storage / Disk Failure
DESCRIPTION: Multiple backup jobs began failing simultaneously with NetBackup status code 2106, indicating the disk storage server has been marked as down. The issue affects all jobs targeting the cloud storage unit backed by AWS S3. The NetBackup CloudStore Service was verified running on the master server but may not be running on the configured media server. Recent certificate maintenance was performed on the media servers last week, which may have left stale or missing NetBackup certificates on one or more media servers.

